Biography

Walter was born in 1892, and baptised 7 Jul 1892 in Holy Trinity, Dover, Kent, England. He was the son of Patrick Doyle and Julia Withers. [1] [2]

In the 1901 census Walter (age 9) was the son of Patrick Doyle in Dover, Kent, England.[3]

In the 1911 census Walter (age 18), shop Porter, was the single son of Julia Doyle at 44 Clarendon Street, Dover, Kent, Dover, England.[4]

Walter was in a British Army World War I Military Record. His service number was 2056.[5]

Pte Walter Doyle was in the Rifle Brigade. His service number was 140, 204493.[6]

In the 1939 register Walter, Hotel Porter, was single in Wampack Hotel Castle Hill Ave, Folkestone, Kent, England.[7]

He married Doris Agnes Hart in 1941, in Dover, Kent, England. [8]

He passed away in 1972, aged 80 years in Dover, Kent, England. [9]
